features.name: mobileOG_000321486|dinB|WP_071730921.1|replication/recombination/repair|NA|Plasmid IMS,IMS_C,IMS_HHH Poorly processive, error-prone DNA polymerase involved in untargeted mutagenesis. Copies undamaged DNA at stalled replication forks, which arise in vivo from mismatched or misaligned primer ends. These misaligned primers can be extended by PolIV. Exhibits no 3'-5' exonuclease (proofreading) activity. May be involved in translesional synthesis, in conjunction with the beta clamp from PolIII

mobileOG_000319248|recU|WP_088911322.1|replication/recombination/repair|NA|Multiple|Homology RecU Endonuclease that resolves Holliday junction intermediates in genetic recombination. Cleaves mobile four-strand junctions by introducing symmetrical nicks in paired strands. Promotes annealing of linear ssDNA with homologous dsDNA. Required for DNA repair, homologous recombination and chromosome segregation
